  <summary date="2015-06-08T19:28:26Z" status="Introduced in Senate">This bill requires that a military working dog be retired in the United States, except when a U.S. citizen living abroad adopts the dog at the time of retirement.

Amounts available to the military department concerned shall be available for such dog's transport to the United States for retirement.</summary>
